<TITLE> Westmont sacks Faruq for 'false case' </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, Jan 7 (bdnews24.com)  Westmont Power (Bangladesh) chairman Tajul Islam Faruq, who had filed an extortion case against Awami League president Sheikh Hasina, has been sacked on charges of "deliberately filing the false case". A press release of the Westmont Power on Wednesday said the board on Jan. 5 decided to remove Tajul Islam from his position. Joseph Chang Chek Ah, managing director of the Westmont Power (Bangladesh) Limited, said the company had no involvement in the filing of the case. Police on Sunday cleared Hasina, now prime minister for a second term, of the charges when it submitted the final report to Dhaka Metropolitan Sessions Judge's Court. Tazul had filed the Tk 3 crore extortion case on Apr. 9, 2008, but on Dec. 23, he appealed to the police to withdraw the case. bdnew
